# Pagination & Filtering Rules

**Note:** This rule provides specific pagination patterns. All implementations must follow `nestjs-architecture.mdc` section 6 for data access patterns.

## Pagination

All list endpoints must support pagination:
- Query parameters: `page` (default: 1), `pageSize` (default: 20, max: 100)
- Response format: `{ count, next, previous, results }`

## Pagination DTO

```typescript
export class PaginationDto {
  @IsOptional()
  @Type(() => Number)
  @Min(1)
  page?: number = 1;

  @IsOptional()
  @Type(() => Number)
  @Min(1)
  @Max(100)
  pageSize?: number = 20;
}
```

## Response Format

```typescript
{
  count: 150,
  next: "https://api.hochu.com/api/requests?page=2",
  previous: null,
  results: [...]
}
```

## Filtering

- Filter through query parameters in DTO
- Support multiple filters simultaneously
- Use Mongoose query methods for filtering

## Sorting

Sorting through `sort` query parameter:
- `sort=createdAt` - Sort by creation date (ASC)
- `sort=-createdAt` - Sort by creation date (DESC)
- `sort=price` - Sort by price (ASC)
- `sort=-price` - Sort by price (DESC)
- `sort=rating` - Sort by rating (ASC)
- `sort=-rating` - Sort by rating (DESC)

## Search

- Text search on `title` and `description` fields using MongoDB text indexes
- Use `$text` operator for text search
- Create text indexes: `Schema.index({ title: 'text', description: 'text' })`
- For complex cases, consider Elasticsearch or Atlas Search

## Implementation

```typescript
async findAll(dto: GetRequestsDto) {
  const page = PaginationUtil.normalizePage(dto.page);
  const pageSize = PaginationUtil.normalizePageSize(dto.pageSize);
  const skip = PaginationUtil.getSkip(page, pageSize);

  const query: any = {};
  
  // Apply filters
  if (dto.category) {
    query.category = dto.category;
  }
  
  if (dto.search) {
    query.$text = { $search: dto.search };
  }
  
  // Build sort object
  let sort: any = { createdAt: -1 };
  if (dto.sort) {
    const order = dto.sort.startsWith('-') ? -1 : 1;
    const field = dto.sort.replace('-', '');
    sort = { [field]: order };
  }
  
  const [results, count] = await Promise.all([
    this.requestModel
      .find(query)
      .sort(sort)
      .skip(skip)
      .limit(pageSize)
      .exec(),
    this.requestModel.countDocuments(query).exec(),
  ]);
  
  return PaginationUtil.createPaginationResult(
    results,
    count,
    page,
    pageSize,
    '/api/requests',
    dto,
  );
}
```
